<table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0 border=0 width=80%>
<tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td>
	<td><font class="pressReleaseBody"><title>Innovations 2000 Awards</title><style>
td {font-family: verdana; font-size: 10px;}
p  {font-family: verdana; font-size: 10px;}
th {font-family: verdana; font-size: 10px; font-weight: bold; color:#ffffff; text-align:left}
</style>
Attendees to the 2000 International CES, 

held today through Sunday, January 9, in Las Vegas, can see the winning 

product entries in the much anticipated Innovations 2000 design contest 

sponsored by the Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) and endorsed by the 

Industrial Designers Society of America (IDSA) and the Consumer Electronics 

Society of the Institute of Electrical and Electronics Engineers (IEEE). The 

contest’s winning products are on display at the Sands Expo and Convention 

Center, and the “Best of Showcase” entries—the best of the best—also appear 

in the Grand Lobby of the Las Vegas Convention Center.

<p>

As the most widely renowned consumer technology awards program, Innovations 

recognizes the best designed and engineered products in the categories of 

accessibility, audio, blank media, computer hardware and software, 

electronic gaming, home data networking, integrated home systems, home 

appliances, home theater, online/Internet, mobile electronics, mobile 

office, personal electronics, photographic equipment, retail resource, 

satellite systems, small office/home office, specialty/high-end audio, 

telephones, video and wireless communications.

<p>

Demonstrating a true sense of imagination and excellence within the consumer 

technology industry, the Best of Showcase winners are:
<p>

<table cellpadding=3 cellspacing=0 border=0>

<tr valign=top bgcolor=444444>

<th>Category</th><th>Product Name</th><th>Company</b></th></tr>

<tr valign=top><td>Audio</td><td>Skip Doctor CDSE-910</td><td>Digital Innovations</td></tr>

<tr valign=top bgcolor=dddddd><td>Computer Hardware</td><td>Stowaway Keyboard</td><td>Think Outside, Inc.</td></tr>

<tr valign=top><td>Home Theater</td><td>Proscan HDTV PS65000</td><td>Thomson Consumer Electronics</td></tr>

<tr valign=top bgcolor=dddddd><td>Integrated Home Systems</td><td>HomePortal 1000 Series</td><td>2Wire Inc.</td></tr>

<tr valign=top><td>Mobile Electronics</td><td>Wireless Headphone System UAH-S2</td><td>Laral Group LLC</td></tr>

<tr valign=top bgcolor=dddddd><td>Online/Internet</td><td>iPhone</td><td>InfoGear Technology Corp.</td></tr>

<tr valign=top><td>Personal Electronics</td><td>AJ3965 CD Clock Radio</td><td>Philips Consumer Electronics</td></tr>

<tr valign=top bgcolor=dddddd><td>Photography</td><td>Cyber-shot™ DSC-F505</td><td>Sony Electronics</td></tr>

<tr valign=top><td>Satellite Systems</td><td>DISHPlayer 500</td><td>EchoStar Technologies Corp.</td></tr>

<tr valign=top bgcolor=dddddd><td>Small Office/Home Office</td><td>CyberGenie CG2400</td><td>Cygnion Corp.</td></tr>

<tr valign=top><td>Specialty Audio</td><td>Super Audio CD™ Player SCD-1</td><td>Sony Electronics</td></tr>

<tr valign=top bgcolor=dddddd><td>Telephones</td><td>BeoCom6000</td><td>Bang & Olufsen America Inc.</td></tr>

<tr valign=top><td>Video</td><td>RCA HDTV F38310</td><td>Thomson Consumer Electronics</td></tr>

<tr valign=top bgcolor=dddddd><td>Wireless Communications</td><td>PCS 8800 Series</td><td>Nokia</td></tr>

</table>

<p>

To qualify for the contest, entrants must exhibit at CES and manufacture 

products marketed in the United States. In addition, the entry must fit 

within the product category in which it is being exhibited, be marketed at 

retail outlets and be commercially available to consumers no later than the 

first quarter of this year.
<p>

These prestigious awards are an opportunity for manufacturers and developers 

to have their products judged by a preeminent panel of journalists, 

designers and engineers, and have the winning products showcased at the 2000 

International CES.  Together, there were 25 judges divided by various 

product categories. Product evaluations are based on weighted criteria, 

including value to users, aesthetics, contributions to the quality of life, 

the product’s innovative qualities and overall excellence. This year there 

were nearly 600 entries.
<p>

Large lucite awards are on display in the winners’ booths at CES, giving 

these companies industry-wide recognition as leaders in their fields. The 

award winners are entitled to use the Innovations 2000 logo on all packaging 

and advertising to identify their company as having achieved excellence in 

product design.
<p>

Winners also 

are listed on www.CESweb.org, the interactive source for CES news and 

information.
<p>

The Consumer Electronics Association (CEA) is a sector of the Electronic 

Industries Alliance (EIA), the 76-year-old Arlington, Virginia-based trade 

organization representing all facets of electronics manufacturing. CEA 

represents more than 500 U.S. manufacturers of audio, video, accessories, 

mobile electronics, communication, information technology and multimedia 

products that are sold through consumer channels.
<p>

As the sponsor, manager and producer of the International CES—Your Source 

for Workstyle and Lifestyle TechnologySM, CEA reinvests all profits from CES 

into industry services, including technical training and education, product 

promotion, engineering standards development, market research, and 

governmental and legal affairs support. As the first major technology event 

of the new millennium, the 2000 International CES is the launch pad for 21st 

century technology.
</font></td></tr>



</table>
